Registering flags
    The code underlying these is annotated in the second option of the CommandText rule (see Command.act)

    asAttributes    every entry in the registry is flagged as an attribute

    components      when registering a group, also register its components

    data            when registering item by its text not its tag. For example, artist=Prince
                    would register Prince because presumably the attribute tag: artist is the
                    name of the registry

    grouped         if a registry is grouped, when you add an attribute from the registry to an
                    item, the item gets added to the registered attribute as well. That is, the
                    attribute becomes a group of every item that contains it as well as being
                    an attribute of the item

    search          add the registry to end of the registry search list

    tagged          when a tagged attribute gets added to an item, the item gets added as
                    a member of the tagged attribute (this is similar to and not compatible
                    with the grouped flag described above. Not sure what the difference is)

    value           When adding an item to the registry, load its value as the tag.
                    When referenced, the tag is resolved to be the registry name. Similar but
                    not quite the same as the data flag. It is used when processing lists that
                    have data but no tag

